[size=14pt][b][color=#FF00FF]🚀 WHAT'S NEW IN v1.0.40-beta[/color][/b][/size]

[size=12pt][b][color=#00FF94]1. Multi-Peer Round-Robin Sync[/color][/b][/size]

[b]Feature:[/b] Distribute sync chunks across multiple peers instead of relying on a single peer.

[b]Implementation:[/b]
[code]pub struct MultiPeerSyncConfig {
    pub max_concurrent_peers: usize,     // Default: 3
    pub rtt_weight_enabled: bool,        // Default: true
    pub failover_timeout_ms: u64,        // Default: 5000
    pub load_balance_strategy: Strategy, // RoundRobin or RTTWeighted
}[/code]

[b]How It Works:[/b]
1. Discover available peers via libp2p Kademlia DHT
2. Measure RTT to each peer dynamically
3. Assign chunks to peers based on RTT (lower RTT = more chunks)
4. Monitor for timeouts and auto-failover to backup peers
5. Aggregate responses and write to database

[b]Performance Impact:[/b]
• [b]2 peers:[/b] +60% throughput (6.76 → 10.8 blocks/s)
• [b]3 peers:[/b] +90% throughput (6.76 → 12.8 blocks/s)
• [b]4+ peers:[/b] Diminishing returns (network becomes bottleneck)

[b]Safety:[/b]
• Each peer response is verified independently
• Malicious/faulty peer responses are rejected
• Automatic fallback to single-peer if multi-peer fails

[size=12pt][b][color=#00FF94]2. Enhanced Metrics & Monitoring[/color][/b][/size]

[b]Feature:[/b] Detailed timing instrumentation for every stage of sync.

[b]Metrics Exported:[/b]
[code]# Prometheus metrics
turbosync_compression_time_ms        # Server-side compression
turbosync_network_transfer_time_ms   # Network round-trip
turbosync_decompression_time_ms      # Client-side decompression
turbosync_database_write_time_ms     # Database write
turbosync_total_chunk_time_ms        # Total per-chunk time
turbosync_peer_rtt_ms                # Per-peer RTT
turbosync_timeout_rate               # Timeout percentage
turbosync_blocks_per_second          # Sustained sync rate[/code]

[b]Dashboard Integration:[/b]
• Grafana dashboard template included
• Real-time visualization of bottlenecks
• Alerts for degraded performance
• Historical trend analysis

[size=12pt][b][color=#00FF94]3. Compression-Level Feature Flag[/color][/b][/size]

[b]Feature:[/b] Runtime-configurable compression level without rebuilding.

[b]Usage:[/b]
[code]# Environment variable
export Q_COMPRESSION_LEVEL=1  # Fast compression (default in v1.0.40)

# Or command-line flag
./q-api-server --compression-level 1

# Or config file
[turbosync]
compression_level = 1  # 1-3 supported[/code]

[b]Levels:[/b]
• [b]Level 1:[/b] Fast (20ms), larger size (+20%), recommended for sync
• [b]Level 2:[/b] Balanced (35ms), medium size (+10%)
• [b]Level 3:[/b] Slow (60ms), smallest size (baseline)

[b]Auto-Tuning (future):[/b] Dynamically adjust based on available bandwidth

